item.title: Knitting Room
item.description:
This little shop is jammed full. Yarn, yarn everywhere. They make the most of every possible nook and cranny. I like this place also because they have a lot of different kinds of knitting needles in all different sizes. Also, the people who work here are younger and hipper than in the other stores I go to. I reccomend buying supplies here and then knitting your way through a good documentary at the Capitol Theater across the street.
Address: 2 lake St, Arlington, MA
Tags: knitting, yarn, pins and needles, handspun, hand dyed, novelty yarn, fancy, simple, young, hip, friendly, needles, addy, cute hats

item.title: Shooting Location for "The Field of Dreams" Film
item.description:
1989's Field of Dreams was a Best Picture Academy Award nominee, and the baseball field in the cornfield still stands today, and has become quite a tourist destination. Games are occasionally played at the field, re-enacting professional baseball at the turn of the 20th Century.
Address: Dyersville, Iowa
Tags: iowa, baseball, movie locations, field of dreams, kevin costner, costner, dyersville, kinsella, james earl jones, chicago black sox, shoeless joe, joe jackson, famous farms, film, movie, cinema, shooting location
